====SOURCE 

https://techcrunch.com/2019/09/13/this-prosthetic-arm-combines-manual-control-with-machine-learning/?guccounter=1&guce_referrer_us=aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZ29vZ2xlLmNvbS8&guce_referrer_cs=1KcP3nVUnYbAjclLNInPJg 

====AGENT 

École polytechnique fédérale de Lausanne (EPFL) 

====GOAL 

Control prosthetic limbs with sensors placed on muscles and other signals. 

====DATA 

Data was retrieved from known biology and testing on patient with their arm amputated above the elbow 

====METHOD 

Sensors are placed on the muscles and other sensors along with machine learning alogorithms. 

====RESULTS 

People with their arm amputated above the elbow will be able to use their prosthetic arm with more functionality. 

====COMMENTS 

With more research in this field the world could be changed for people with life changing ailments. 